# Response Footer Convention

## Convention Summary

All agents MUST end their responses with a standardized footer that documents affected files, current task context, role, and target audience. This provides transparency and traceability for all agent actions.

## Rules

### Footer Structure

- ✅ MUST include 3 separator lines (48 dashes each)
- ✅ MUST include "Affected files" section
- ✅ MUST include task/role metadata section
- ✅ MUST list files added, modified, deleted (or "None" for each)
- ✅ MUST specify current task file if working on a task
- ✅ MUST specify role and agent identifier
- ✅ MUST specify target audience with model name
- ❌ MUST NOT omit any required sections
- ❌ MUST NOT use shortened format

### File Lists

- ✅ MUST categorize as Added, Modified, or Deleted
- ✅ MUST use relative paths from repository root
- ✅ MUST list each file on separate line or comma-separated
- ✅ MUST write "None" if category is empty
- ❌ MUST NOT omit empty categories

### Metadata

- ✅ MUST include Task file path (if applicable)
- ✅ MUST include Role in backticks
- ✅ MUST include Agent Identifier
- ✅ MUST include Target Audience with model name
- ⚠️ MAY include additional context (commit hash, status, etc.)

## Examples

### ✅ Good Example - Standard Footer

```markdown
------------------------------------------------

### Affected files

**Added**:
- Configuration/ConventionFormat.md
- Convention/Convention.convention.template

**Modified**:
- Framework/Implementation.prompt.md
- Configuration/StructuredConceptPattern.md

**Deleted**: None

------------------------------------------------

> **Task**: Git/AiSliceMigration.task
> **Role**: `Implementer`
> **Agent Identifier**: `Implementation Agent`
> **Target Audience**: `Strategic Agent (Reviewer)`

------------------------------------------------
```

### ✅ Good Example - No Active Task

```markdown
------------------------------------------------

### Affected files

**Added**: None

**Modified**:
- README.md
- .github/copilot-instructions.md

**Deleted**: None

------------------------------------------------

> **Task**: Continuous Flow (Orchestrator)
> **Role**: `Orchestrator`
> **Agent Identifier**: `Strategic Agent`
> **Target Audience**: `User`

------------------------------------------------
```

### ❌ Bad Example - Missing Sections

```markdown
Files changed:
- Configuration/ConventionFormat.md (added)
- README.md (modified)

Role: Implementer
```

**Problems**:
- Missing separator lines
- Incomplete file categorization
- Missing task reference
- Missing target audience
- Informal format

### ❌ Bad Example - Wrong Format

```markdown
---
Changed files: ConventionFormat.md, README.md
Role: Implementer, Task: AiSliceMigration.task
---
```

**Problems**:
- Using YAML format instead of markdown
- Not separating Added/Modified/Deleted
- Missing Agent Identifier
- Missing Target Audience

## Validation

### Manual Verification

- [ ] Three separator lines present (48 dashes each)
- [ ] "Affected files" section with Added/Modified/Deleted
- [ ] Each category lists files or says "None"
- [ ] Task file specified (or "Continuous Flow")
- [ ] Role in backticks
- [ ] Agent Identifier present
- [ ] Target Audience with model name

### Template

```markdown
------------------------------------------------

### Affected files

**Added**: {List or None}
**Modified**: {List or None}
**Deleted**: {List or None}

------------------------------------------------

> **Task**: {TaskFile.task or context}
> **Role**: `{AssignedRole}`
> **Agent Identifier**: `{AgentId}`
> **Target Audience**: `{TargetRole} ({Model})`

------------------------------------------------
```

