## Markdown Code Block Nesting

**Rule**: When producing markdown containing code blocks, always validate backtick nesting depth.

**Validation**:
- Outer block backtick count MUST be > inner block backtick count
- GitHub markdown maximum nesting: 4 backticks
- Use alternative formatting (bullet points, plain text) when nesting would break

**Common Scenarios**:

| Scenario | Outer | Inner | Valid? |
|----------|-------|-------|--------|
| PR comment with delegation | 3 backticks | Bullet points | ✅ |
| Task file delegation block | N/A (file) | 4 backticks | ✅ |
| Nested code examples | 4 backticks | 3 backticks | ✅ |
| Broken nesting | 3 backticks | 4 backticks | ❌ |

**Best Practice**: When embedding delegation prompts in PR comments, use bullet-point format instead of nested code blocks.
